title git notes remove does NOT erase history
edge applies-to tree:af60d1f32d1ccdb3dff2025eea5a2e49ea8819c8
edge targets-treepath treepath:.

Removing a note creates a new commit on the notes ref that deletes it,
but the old commit that ADDED it stays in git log --all. A secret once
written to any notes ref is permanent in the history. gitleaks will find
it on every subsequent scan.

This is git's design, not a mycelium bug. But it means: never write
secrets to notes, even temporarily. There is no undo.
